            "accordion_row_seo2": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_dash_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "How does 10Cr15CoMoV compare to VG10?",
                "content": "<p>They're very similar in composition and performance. Both achieve 60 HRC hardness, both contain vanadium for wear resistance and cobalt for heat hardness. The main difference is origin: VG10 is made by Takefu Special Steel in Japan, while 10Cr15CoMoV is produced in China. In blind testing, most users cannot distinguish between the two. Read our <a href=\"/blogs/news/vg10-steel-vs-10cr15comov-guide\">VG10 vs 10Cr15CoMoV comparison</a> for the full breakdown.</p>",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
