              "settings": {
                "heading": "How often should I sharpen a Retro Series knife?",
                "content": "<p>With regular honing, most home cooks can go 4-6 months between whetstone sharpenings. The 60 HRC steel holds an edge well but responds quickly to a 1000/6000 combination stone when it does need attention. See our <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-sharpen-knives-whetstone\">whetstone sharpening guide</a> for step-by-step instructions.</p>",
